-- Slovenia Leading U.S. 2-0 in First Half of World Cup Game in Johannesburg
-- Bob Bensch
-- 2010-06-18T14:42:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-18/slovenia-leading-u-s-2-0-in-first-half-of-world-cup-game-in-johannesburg.html

          
          
             Slovenia leads the U.S. 2-0 in the
first half of their World Cup Group C game in Johannesburg on
goals from Valter Birsa and Zlatan Ljubijankic.  
 The U.S. tied England 1-1 in its opening game and Slovenia
beat Algeria 1-0. England faces Algeria later today. Serbia
defeated Germany 1-0 earlier in Group D.  
          
          


  


        